{"questionId":"12180","questionHtml":"<p>Show that <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{b}{{\\sqrt {{a^2} + {b^2}} }} = {\\text{cos}}\\,\\theta \">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>b</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>a</mi>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>b</mi>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>cos</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>θ</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong> EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>use of a right triangle and Pythgoras’ to show the missing side length is <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\">\n  <mi>b</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>Use of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{si}}{{\\text{n}}^2}\\theta&nbsp; + {\\text{co}}{{\\text{s}}^2}\\theta&nbsp; = 1\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>si</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>n</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mi>θ</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>co</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>s</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mi>θ</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;leading to the required result&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12180","referenceCode":"EXM.3.AHL.TZ0.5f.i","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that b a 2 + b 2 = cos θ .","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"f.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.7—Circular functions: graphs, composites, transformations","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.10—Compound angle identities"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}